5000|$|The {{rules are}} the same for larger numbers, e.g. 1,000,000 złotych; 1,000,002 złote; 1,000,011 złotych; 1,000,024 złote. Fractions should be {{rendered}} with word złotego [...] and grosza , e.g. 0,1 złotego; 2,5 złotego, etc. It is customary in Poland to use <b>space</b> (<b>non-breaking)</b> for digit grouping (“thousands separator”) and comma for separating fractions from whole numbers; cf. decimal mark.|$|R
